{{Infobox language |name=Budu |nativename= |states=[[China]] |region=[[Yunnan]] |ethnicity=10,000 [[Hani people|Hani]] (1998)<ref name=AH>[http://asiaharvest.org/wp-content/themes/asia/docs/people-groups/China/chinaPeoples/B/Budo.pdf]</ref><!--later pop figures just extrapolated, which obscures the fact that this is a very rough estimate.--> |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Southern Loloish languages|Southern]] |fam6=[[Hani languages|Hani]] |fam7=[[Honi language|Hao-Bai]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Budu''' ({{zh|布都}}) is a [[Hanoish languages|Southern]] [[Loloish language]] of [[Yunnan]], China. Budu is spoken in [[Jiangcheng Hani and Yi Autonomous County]], [[Mojiang Hani Autonomous County]], [[Zhenyuan Yi, Hani and Lahu Autonomous County]], and [[Yuanjiang Hani, Yi and Dai Autonomous County]].
Many Budu born after c. 1970 are unable to speak the language.<ref name=AH/>
