The '''Dilling''' are an ethnic group of the [[Nuba peoples]]. The Dilling number several thousand and live mainly in the [[Nuba Mountains]] of [[South Kordofan|South Kordofan state]], in southern [[Sudan]].
==Language== The [[Dilling language]] is one of the [[Nubian languages]] of the [[Nilo-Saharan languages|Nilo-Saharan]] family. The Dilling language has become partially arabized. {{Citation needed|date=August 2011}}
